    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Github's dependabot warns us that it cannot update `highlight.js` to a non-vulnerable version.\r\n\r\nThe latest possible version that can be installed is 9.18.5 because of the following conflicting dependencies:\r\n```\r\n@nomiclabs/hardhat-truffle5@2.0.0 requires highlight.js@^9.15.8 via a transitive dependency on @truffle/debug-utils@4.2.9\r\n@nomiclabs/hardhat-truffle5@2.0.0 requires highlight.js@^9.12.0 via a transitive dependency on @trufflesuite/chromafi@2.2.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe earliest fixed version is 10.4.1.\r\n\r\nVulnerability details: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-7wwv-vh3v-89cq\r\n\r\nIt's worth noting that the last time I performed memory dump while running a hardhat script there was a lot of memory used by highlight.js. I don't know why this library is used while running scripts, perhaps some bloat inherited from truffle. Hopefully upgrading truffle to a newer version could fix this :grimacing:.\r\n\r\n",
